gomodel:SYNGO_719  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: SNAP= soluble N-ethylmaleimide fusion protein attachment protein.\nSubcellular fractionation and Western Blot with an isoform-specific antibody against beta-SNAP indicates that beta-SNAP is present in membrane and soluble fractions of synaptosomes (Fig.3).\n\nImmunohistochemical analysis indicates the presence of betaSNAP predominantly in synapse-rich regions (e.g. stratum radiatum in the hippocampus, Fig. 4). Pre-embedding electron microscopy of tissue sections and crude synaptic membranes indicates the presence of beta-SNAP in presynaptic plasma membranes, but also postsynaptic densities (Fig. 5+6).\n\nIsoform-specific anti-SNAP antibodies were raised to the sequence: C)SIQGDGEGDGDLK (anti-β-SNAP, residues 286-298 of β-SNAP). Immunoblotting analysis demonstrates the specificity of the antibody (Fig.1). Experimental description: Subcellular fractions of rat brain homogenate were prepared according to procedures originally described by..." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" ;
        dc:date           "2017-06-06" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_719" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

